A 32-year-old suspect has been arrested in the case of seven people killed at a house in Khayelitsha. Seven others, including a six-year-old girl, were injured. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police have arrested a 32-year-old man from Khayelitsha after seven people were shot and killed in a brazen attack by gunmen in the early hours of Sunday morning. Seven more people were injured, including a six-year-old child. READ: Patients turned away following burglary at Khayelitsha clinic Police say more arrests for the mass shooting are imminent. “A team of experienced detectives assigned to the cases has made an arrest today," Brigadier Novela Potelwa. "The suspect 32 who is from Khayelitsha is expected in court soon. More arrests are imminent as the investigations progress.” READ: Alex residents outraged after woman shot dead allegedly by police Families of the injured say they are still in shock. Locals believe the shootings in Khayelitsha are gang-related. There have been at least three shootings in at illegal taverns in Khayelitsha since the beginning of the year and more than 10 people have lost their lives to date.